storeDetailedDescription: The Burley Bee is the perfect bike trailer for parents looking for a high-quality, no-frills trailer for occasional use. The Bee holds either one or two children, safe and snug inside the 5-point harness, full-perimeter aluminum frame, and gap-free nylon fabric panels. The Bee is backed by a solid three year warranty (the best in its class), and is amazingly easy to fold down flat for storage or transport.

storeDescription:
Burley Nomad cargo trailer.
Some other standout features include a flexible hitch connector on a removable tongue.
storeDetailedDescription: The folks over at Burley have really put a lot of thought into the Nomad cargo trailer. Instead of following suit on the other well-known trailer brands, Burly designed a two-wheel cargo trailer that packs a whopping 8000 cubic inches of storage at a 100 pound weight capacity. That means not only can you bring the entire contents of your gear closet on your adventure but the kitchen sink as well. The sharp-looking Nomad has stretchy nylon over a lightweight aluminum frame and comes standard with a water tight tonneau cover to protect your gear. If you are an organizational freak like me, you will really appreciate the interior layout that includes 2 mesh pockets on a convertible divider.

storeDetailedDescription: This bright flavorful wine was produced from six individual blocks of Chardonnay. Stainless Steel and barrel fermentation with multiple yeast strains, French oak barrel aging on the yeast lees, and partial secondary or malolactic fermentation all combine to present a flavorful and complex wine. Aromas of mandarin orange, pineapple and a hint of lemon combine with rich apple and pear flavors. The wine finishes with great flavor and length.

The First Wine of the Vintage! A white counterpart to Nouveau Beaujolais. New Gewürz accentuates the inherent, unique characteristics of the Gewürztraminer grape. To capture and enhance the lively, spicy character of this varietal, we cold-ferment the chilled juice then immediately bottle the wine. 

New Gewürz is the perfect holiday aperitif and mealtime complement.

Brimming with aromas of peach, apricot and honeysuckle, and loaded with lush flavors of pear, honey and vanilla. AVV Viognier has a rich, viscous mouthfeel that envelops the palate in its flavors. This wine is excellent as an apertif or served with shellfish or Asian influenced cuisine.

Cyrus is our limited production, handcrafted, proprietary red wine from the Wetzel Family Estate. Displaying rich, concentrated fruit, spicy oak, a velvety mouth feel and a lasting finish, the 1998 Cyrus is a testament to ourestate grown grapes and fine winemaking. This wine displays intense aromas of black cherry, plum, cassis and chocolate. Firm tannins and a long finish balance the full mouth feel.

The 2000 CYRUS represents our sixth vintage of this now nationally acclaimed wine. 

Composed of 60% Cabernet Sauvignon, 34% Merlot, and 6% Petit Verdot, this latest rendition of CYRUS exploits the nearly perfect growing conditions of the renowned Alexander Valley. The tremendous amount of fruit flavors, including black cherry, plum and cassis are matched perfectly with a like amount of spicy oak. The velvety mouth-feel is similarly complemented by firm yet not unyeilding tannins. Aged both in American and French oak for twenty-four months and twelve months in the bottle prior to release, this wine is at once enjoyable and age-worthy for at least a decade.

Displaying rich, concentrated fruit, spicy oak, a velvety mouth feel, and a lasting finish, the 2001 Cyrus is a testament to estate grown Alexander Valley grapes and fine winemaking. The 2001 CYRUS is composed of 57% Cabernet Sauvignon, 32% Merlot and 11% Cabernet Franc. You will experience intense aromas of black cherry, plum, cassis and chocolate. Firm tannins and a long finish balance the full mouth feel. Balanced to drink now, but long aging will be rewarded.

The color is dark ruby red. Aromas of black cherries, cassis, plum & cedar dominate the nose, along with a hint of anise. The fruit from each Wetzel Estate Vineyard was vinified and treated differently.
The Cabernet Sauvignon, Merlot, and Cabernet Franc grapes for this blend were picked at the peak of ripeness and have excellent natural acidity.
The use of selected Bordeaux yeast strains, high fermentation temperatures and frequent (twice daily) pump-overs made highly extracted wines with intense Bordeaux aromas and flavors yet soft well integrated tannins.

Our benchmark wine since 1976. Medium to full-bodied, this Cabernet displays abundant cherry and currant fruit on the palate and a velvety mouth feel. Supple and polished throughout, it finishes with firm tannins. As with previous vintages, this is an extremely drinkable Cabernet Sauvignon, yet will age for 10-15 years

2002 Wetzel Family Estate Merlot offers classic cassis and black cherry flavors and soft, ripe tannins. Aromas of blackberry and cassis fill the glass with nuances of vanilla and cedar. On the palate this wine is deeply flavored with a hefty core of fruit.

Long, warm summer days and cool evenings during grape maturation along with low yields in our vineyards situated on the Alexander Valley Vineyards property right on the Russian River has unquestionably produced a Pinot Noir which is abundant in the classic Pinot aromas and flavors. Cold soaking; two pump overs a day during fermentation; plus the use of the two different yeast strains enhanced the aroma and flavor.

Aromas of sour cherry, and plum dominate with overtones of tea leaves and dried rose petals. On the palate, flavors of red plum and spice are framed with a supple mouthfeel and medium tannins. This spicy and fruity wine is a perfect accompaniment to any California/Italian cuisine.

With hints of black pepper and currant, this Syrah is
from one of the most interesting sites for Syrah. Garys’ Vineyard is one of
the coolest vineyard locations in the state where Syrah develops rich fruit
and spice flavors. There is wonderful structure and intensity in this wine.

92% Zinfandel and 8% Sangiovese 
The color is deep ruby. Black cherry and plum dominates the bouquet, followed by aromas of crushed black pepper and wild strawberry. Eucalyptus, cedar and cola fill the palate. The wine finishes with subtle oak nuances and integrated acid balance. This is a medium bodied wine with a cellar life of 5-8 years.

Redemption Zinfandel is from the Dry Creek Appellation and displays the classic aromas of ripe blueberries and spice. Blackberries fill the palate supported with a black pepper backbone. The wine finishes with oak nuances and integrated acid balance. This is a medium bodied wine with deep ruby color and a projected cellar life of 5-9 years.

Two Barrel is the evolution of a unique collaboration. In the Spring of 1999, our Wine Club Members, with a little help from our wine making team, were challenged to create a special wine for themselves. Many were tried, but none were as true as a Syrah based blend. Only 500 cases were produced, and it sold out immediately. With a nod toward that original blend, we now produce Two Barrel. This second release is 50% Syrah and 50% Merlot. The Syrah lends aromas of blueberry, violets and earth to this well-structured blend, while Merlot contributes black cherry and cassis to the mid-palate; soft tannins and flavors of plum, oak and chocolate round out the finish. The grapes for this unique blend are harvested from our winemaker’s selection of vineyards, crushed, fermented and aged separately, then blended after fourteen months in French and American oak barrels.

50% Merlot, 35% Cabernet Franc, 15% Cabernet Sauvignon. This wine is based on the winning blend created by Wine Club Members at the 2003 Wine Club Spring Bash. 

The color is dark garnet with a purple tinge. Initial aromas of plum and cassis lead into notes of eucalyptus and cedar. The wine enters with flavors of black cherry and blackberry. Slight hints of varietal earthiness and black olives provide additional complexity to this already intensely aromatic wine. The finish is appeallingly long and elegant with approachable tannins.
